---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

// Plain-language terms of use. Reasonable starter for an early-stage
// Australian SaaS — covers account responsibility, subscription /
// cancellation, acceptable use, liability, governing law. Before
// going live for real money, get this reviewed by a lawyer; the
// substance is fine but specific jurisdictions and edge cases (data
// breach notification, refund disputes, etc.) deserve professional
// language tuned to your situation.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — Beme"
  description="The plain-language terms covering how you use Beme."
>
  <article class="container-tight max-w-3xl mx-auto" style="padding-top: clamp(5rem, 7vw, 9rem); padding-bottom: clamp(4rem, 6vw, 6rem);">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-beme-400 font-semibold mb-4">
      Legal
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-ink-50 tracking-tight">
      Terms of Use
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-400 mt-3">
      Last updated: June 2026
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-[16px] text-ink-200 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <p>
          These terms cover how you use Beme. By creating an account
          or using the software, you agree to them. If you don't
          agree, don't use it. We can update these terms; if we make
          a material change, we'll let active subscribers know by
          email.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Your account</h2>
        <p>
          You're responsible for your account credentials and for
          anything that happens under your account. Don't share login
          details. If you think your account's been used by someone
          who shouldn't have access, get in touch and we'll help.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Subscriptions + cancellation</h2>
        <p>
          Beme is sold as a monthly subscription. We charge your
          payment method at the start of each billing cycle. You can
          cancel at any time from your account settings — your access
          continues until the end of the current paid period, then
          stops. We don't issue partial refunds on cancellation.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If you upgrade or downgrade, we adjust the next billing
          cycle accordingly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Your projects + data</h2>
        <p>
          Anything you build in Beme belongs to you. We store your
          project data so the software works, and we'll only use it
          to provide the service you're paying for. You can export
          your projects as PDFs at any time. If you cancel, your
          data stays accessible for 30 days; after that it may be
          deleted. See the
          <a href="/legal/privacy" class="text-beme-400 hover:text-beme-300 underline">
            Privacy Policy
          </a>
          for how we handle it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>
          Don't use Beme to do anything illegal, infringe other
          people's rights, or try to break the service for other
          users. Don't try to reverse-engineer the software or
          resell it as your own.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">No warranty on estimates</h2>
        <p>
          Beme produces quantity estimates from the data you input.
          We work hard to make those calculations accurate, but you
          are responsible for verifying your estimates before you
          order materials or sign a contract. Beme is a tool that
          helps you estimate; it's not a guarantee, and we're not
          liable for losses caused by ordering errors, supplier
          pricing, or how the estimate gets used downstream.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the extent allowed by law, our liability for any claim
          related to your use of Beme is capped at the amount you've
          paid us in the twelve months before the claim. We're not
          liable for indirect losses (lost profits, lost data,
          downtime impacts) where the law allows that limit.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Changes + termination</h2>
        <p>
          We can change or discontinue parts of the service with
          reasonable notice. We can also suspend or terminate an
          account that breaks these terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of Queensland,
          Australia. Any disputes will be handled in Queensland
          courts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Questions</h2>
        <p>
          Email
          <a href="mailto:hello@beme.com.au" class="text-beme-400 hover:text-beme-300 underline">
            hello@beme.com.au
          </a>
          and we'll get back to you.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
